<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="67" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,727,1604]" pageId="8" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,340,1462,1488]" pageId="8" pageNumber="67">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[351,528,1463,1488]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="disparifrons" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[351,528,1463,1488]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="67">A. disparifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[538,607,1462,1488]" pageId="8" pageNumber="67">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[538,607,1462,1488]" pageId="8" pageNumber="67" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Knull, 1941" authorityName="Knull" authorityYear="1941" box="[771,1048,1462,1488]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limpiae">
<emphasis box="[771,895,1463,1488]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="67">A. limpiae</emphasis>
Knull, 
<number box="[989,1048,1462,1488]" pageId="8" pageNumber="67" value="1941.0">1941</number>
</taxonomicName>
described from the southcentral 
<collectingCountry box="[151,316,1501,1527]" name="United States of America" pageId="8" pageNumber="67">United States</collectingCountry>
(Kansas, Oklahoma, Texas), but differs by these principal characters: smaller dimensions, premarginal carinula absent, marginal carinae of pronotum subparallel, not joined at base, presence of a pubescent dimple at base of frons, and aedeagus slender and lengthened.
</paragraph>
